------------------------------
Branch       : galliumos-xfce/2017
Distribution : GalliumOS 2.1
Computer     : Acer C720
Begin date   : Sept. 2017
------------------------------
* Preconfiguration

- Update and upgrade system
  > sudo apt update
  > sudo apt dist-upgrade

- Install Git
  `> sudo apt install git
     git config --global user.name "Anthony Vallee"
     git config --global user.email "tony.vallee@hotmail.com"
  `

- Install Zsh and Oh My Zsh
  `> sudo apt install zsh
     chsh -s $(which zsh)
     sh -c "$(curl -fsSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/robbyrussell/oh-my-zsh/master/tools/install.sh)"
  `

- Import .dotfiles config
  `> rm ~/.zshrc && ln -s ~/.dotfiles/.zshrc ~/.zshrc
     ln -s ~/.dotfiles/.zshenv ~/.zshenv
     source ~/.zshenv && source ~/.zshrc
  `

- Install Powerline fonts
  `> cd ~/Downloads
     git clone https://github.com/powerline/fonts.git --depth=1
     cd fonts
     ./install.sh
     cd ..
     rm -rf fonts
  `

- Install Emacs
  `> sudo add-apt-repository ppa:kelleyk/emacs
     sudo apt-get update
     sudo apt-get install emacs25
  `

- Install Spacemacs
  `> rm -rf ~/.emacs.d
     git clone https://github.com/syl20bnr/spacemacs ~/.emacs.d
     emacs
  `
  - Exit Emacs after Spacemacs is installed
  > ln -s ~/.dotfiles/.spacemacs ~/.spacemacs

- Run emacs daemon with systemd
  `> cp ~/.dotfiles/.config/systemd/user/emacs.service ~/.config/systemd/user/emacs.service
     sudo systemctl enable --user emacs
     sudo systemctl start --user emacs
  `

- Fetch configuration
  > git clone https://github.com/anthonyvallee/dotfiles.git ~/.dotfiles
  > git checkout galliumos-xfce/2017

------------------------------
* Configuration

- Apply keyboard layout configuration
  > cp ~/.dotfiles/.config/xfce4/xfconf/xfce-perchannel-xml/keyboard-layout.xml ~/.config/xfce4/xfconf/xfce-perchannel-xml/keyboard-layout.xml
  - (Optional) Reboot to apply changes.
